<div id="review_47832667" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/47832667" />
    <a title="Ally" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1802446-ally"><img alt="Ally" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1229281358p2/1802446.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/47832667?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ally" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ally" href="/user/show/1802446-ally">Ally</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780375828249" href="/book/show/307792.The_People_of_Sparks">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer47832667" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1999855015237138768">A sequel that holds true to its original characters, but puts them in a totally different situation and set of adventures. If I had one problem with these books, it would be that I suspect the authour starts writing the books with a &quot;what values can I leave the readers with?&quot; idea in her head. But, to her credit, I usually agree with her values (avoiding crowd mentality, being tolerant, solving problems non-violently) and the story is exciting enough anyways.</span>
  <span id="freeText1999855015237138768" style="display:none">A sequel that holds true to its original characters, but puts them in a totally different situation and set of adventures. If I had one problem with these books, it would be that I suspect the authour starts writing the books with a "what values can I leave the readers with?" idea in her head. But, to her credit, I usually agree with her values (avoiding crowd mentality, being tolerant, solving problems non-violently) and the story is exciting enough anyways.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1999855015237138768" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


